This is a good argument against ever uploading RARs or other archives; if this were -- for example -- just an MP4 it would be possible to watch pretty much the whole movie by just skipping through a few scenes where there's missing data.   As soon as the thing is RAR'd, though, every minute of the movie becomes dependent on every other minute, unless there's some better unRARing utility that I'm unaware of that can deal with incomplete files.
